The 22-year-old Cape Town woman was killed allegedly because she was a lesbian. CAPE TOWN - Police have confirmed a man has been arrested in connection with the murder of a 22-year-old woman who was killed allegedly because she was a lesbian.Noluvo Swelindawo's body was found near Khayelitsha, close to the N2 highway, a few days after she was abducted from her Driftsands home.Police say a 24-year-old man will appear in the Blue Downs Magistrates Court on kidnapping and murder charges on Wednesday.Police spokesperson FC Van Wyk said: Our investigation into the murder of Noluvo led to the arrest of the suspect on Monday afternoon. He will appear in court on Friday on charges of murder and kidnapping. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)